HEADWORD: Metempirics
<hw>Met`em*pir"ics</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The concepts
and relations which are conceived as beyond, and yet as related to, the
knowledge gained by experience.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Metempsychose</ent>⟦br⟧
